The paper deals with deep learning theory and regularization techniques for deep neural networks, which are primarily studied in the machine learning subfield of computer science. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also heavily relies on information theory concepts, such as Fisher information, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as the second most likely sub-category. The experiments are performed on image datasets, indicating the relevance to computer vision, hence cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a metric for generalizability, which is a common problem in neural networks, suggesting cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a regularization technique, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category.
